  "description": {
    "en-US": "Aquinas's commentary on the *Liber de Causis* — the Neoplatonic compilation derived from Proclus's *Elements of Theology*. Aquinas was the first medieval to identify its source as Proclus rather than Aristotle.",
    "la": "Expositio Thomae in *Librum de Causis* — compilationem Neoplatonicam ex *Elementatione Theologica* Procli derivatam. Thomas primus medii aevi fontem eius Proclum, non Aristotelem esse identificavit."
  },
  "composed": "1271–1272",
